item.title: [HIVE-13882] When hive.server2.async.exec.async.compile is turned on, from JDBC we will get "The query did not generate a result set"
item.description:
The following would fail with "The query did not generate a result set"

stmt.execute("SET hive.driver.parallel.compilation=true");
stmt.execute("SET hive.server2.async.exec.async.compile=true");
ResultSet res = stmt.executeQuery("SELECT * FROM " + tableName);
res.next();
item.summary: When hive.server2.async.exec.async.compile is turned on, from JDBC we will get "The query did not generate a result set"

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Patch-1: add hasResultSet field in OperationStatus so when the query finishes, we will get accurate hasResultSet.
+Jimmy Xiang Notice that you enabled compile inside the session.

Patch-2: address comments.
Thanks. +1
